setSelectedPtnPinBlk(25.10)                        setSelectedPtnPinBlk(25.10)

Name
       setSelectedPtnPinBlk  -  Sets  the area, name, and layer ID for the se-
       lected partition pin blockage

Syntax
       setSelectedPtnPinBlk

       [-help]

       <x1><y1><x2><y2>

       <PtnPinBlkName>

       {<layerID>}

       Sets the area, name, and layer ID for the selected partition pin block-
       age.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setSelectedPtnPinBlk parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setSelectedPtnPinBlk

       <x1> <y1> <x2> <y2>
              Specifies the coordinates of the partition pin blockage area.

       <PtnPinBlkName>
              Specifies the name of the partition pin blockage.

       <layerID>
              Specifies the metal layer(s) where partition pins are not to  be
              created.

Example
              * The following command sets the partition pin blockage, ptnPin-
                Blk2,  within the specified area and on the layers 4 (Metal4),
                5 (Metal5), and 6 (Metal6):

                setSelectedPtnPinBlk 100.0 100.0 150.0 150.0 ptnPinBlk2  {4  5
                6}

